    %h3.black
      Now start preparing our web page
  .whitespace
  %p.black
    Let us create an online back bone for a grocery shop. So we need a survey asking what the user need.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('create_a_page_on_our_site.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 600px')
    .clearfix
    .whitespace
  %p.black
    Go to survey tab and create a new survey.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('create_a_survey.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 450px')
    .clearfix
  %p.black
    After creating survey, go to dashboard. Create few single line questions.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('ask_what_the_user_want.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 400px')
    .clearfix
  %p.black
    You can check the preview on the dashboard.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('the_survey_will_look_like_this.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 600px')
    .clearfix
  %p.black
    Now go to one of the pages you have created and pin the new survey.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('the_site_will_look_like_this.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 600px')
    .clearfix
  %p.black
    You can see survey responses at the dashboard.
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('we_can_see_response_to_surveys_at_dasdboard.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 600px')
    .clearfix
  %p.black
    Or on an independent page with all signup form responses
    .clearfix
    = image_tag(image_url('we_will_see_survey_response_along_with_sign_up_form_response.png'), style: 'width: 100%; max-width: 600px')
